<h1>CoAmoebae in 3-space</h1>
<font size="+2"> 
 Mounir Nisse and 
 <a href="http://www.math.tamu.edu/~sottile/index.html">Frank
Sottile</a>
</font><br>
<font size="+1">
A <i>coamoeba</i> is the image of a subvariety of the torus
(<b>C</b>&#42;)<sup><i>n</i></sup> under the argument map to
(<b>S</b><sup>1</sup>)<sup><i>n</i></sup>.
CoAmoebae exhibit structure that is both polyhdral and curvilinear.
Below, we show the coamoebae of a line and a plane in (<b>C</b>&#42;)<sup>3</sup>.
The links are to further pictures and discussion.
</font>
